{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":217367,"duration_api_ms":217322,"ttft_ms":177637,"ttft_stream_ms":5417,"time_to_request_ms":35,"num_turns":2,"result":"I've completed the Phase 9A cross-run queue follow-up review. Here's a summary of what I found:\n\n## Review Result\n\n**All five medium-finding fixes are correctly implemented** per the diff evidence:\n1. ✅ Requeue precondition requires referenced job to be `\"queued\"`\n2. ✅ Already-terminal jobs mirror status instead of recording spurious failures\n3. ✅ Atomic `mkdir(exist_ok=False)` replaces check-then-act, with cleanup-on-failure\n4. ✅ `Draft202012Validator.check_schema` added to static contracts\n5. ✅ Docs clarify queue records are diagnostic-only coordination artifacts\n\n**Two remaining medium risks** identified:\n\n1. **Lossy terminal-status mapping** — Any non-`\"succeeded\"` terminal status collapses to `\"failed\"` in the queue entry. If `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES` includes states like `\"skipped\"` or `\"abandoned\"`, the audit trail would mislabel intentionally-not-run jobs as failures. The test only exercises `succeeded → succeeded`.\n\n2. **Unhandled `load_job_payload` in run-once** — Before the fix, `try_claim_job` returning `None` always reached `mark_cross_run_queue_entry_terminal`. The new intermediate `load_job_payload` call can raise (concurrent deletion/corruption), propagating without releasing the claim or marking the entry terminal — stranding it in `\"claimed\"` until manual recovery. The diff context doesn't show a surrounding `finally` that would mitigate this.\n\n**No high or critical risks** were found in the diff. The primary residual risks are local-filesystem atomicity limitations (documented as a non-goal), crash-during-creation robustness, and the operational burden of manual recovery for stuck entries.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f08bb5af-e2d7-4958-afe4-afff1425dc7a","total_cost_usd":0.53112,"usage":{"input_tokens":43847,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":32320,"output_tokens":11829,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"glm-5.2[1m]":{"inputTokens":43847,"outputTokens":11829,"cacheReadInputTokens":32320,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.53112,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"The Phase 9A follow-up diff addresses five medium findings from the first review, all correctly implemented per the diff evidence: (1) requeue recovery now requires the referenced run-local job to still be \"queued\", (2) run-once mirrors already-terminal referenced job status instead of recording spurious failures, (3) entry creation uses atomic mkdir(exist_ok=False) instead of check-then-act, with cleanup-on-failure, (4) static schema contracts now call Draft202012Validator.check_schema, and (5) state-authority/evidence docs clarify queue records are diagnostic-only coordination artifacts. New tests (terminal mirroring, requeue precondition, abandon clears claim, worker-id authorization, CLI command existence) provide good behavioral coverage. Two remaining medium risks concern lossy terminal-status mapping and unhandled load_job_payload exceptions in the run-once path. No high or critical risks were identified in the diff.","findings":[{"severity":"medium","title":"Lossy non-succeeded terminal status mapping to queue entry \"failed\"","evidence":"In cross_run_queue_run_once, when try_claim_job returns None and the referenced job is terminal, the code maps terminal status as: `terminal_entry_status = (\"succeeded\" if terminal_job_status == \"succeeded\" else \"failed\")`. Any terminal status other than \"succeeded\" (e.g., \"skipped\", \"abandoned\", \"cancelled\") is collapsed to \"failed\". The TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES set is not visible in the diff, so the full set of affected statuses cannot be confirmed. The test only exercises the succeeded -> succeeded path. A job intentionally skipped or abandoned by the owning run would appear as a queue \"failure\", mislabeling the audit trail and potentially misleading operators during diagnosis.","recommendation":"Either enumerate terminal statuses explicitly (map \"succeeded\" -> \"succeeded\", \"skipped\"/\"abandoned\" -> \"skipped\"/\"abandoned\", genuine failures -> \"failed\"), or record the raw terminal_job_status alongside the queue entry status so the original job terminal state is preserved in the entry details without being lost to a binary succeeded/failed collapse.","file":"harness/cli.py","line":2550},{"severity":"medium","title":"Unhandled load_job_payload exceptions in run-once can strand claimed queue entries","evidence":"In cross_run_queue_run_once, when job_claim is None, the new code calls `current_job = load_job_payload(run_dir / \"jobs\" / claimed_entry[\"job_id\"] / \"job.json\")` without local try/except. Before this fix, the None branch went directly to mark_cross_run_queue_entry_terminal(...), guaranteeing the entry was always marked terminal. The new intermediate load_job_payload call introduces a failure window: if the job file is concurrently deleted or corrupted between try_claim_job and load_job_payload, the exception propagates without releasing the queue claim or recording a terminal status. The entry remains stuck in \"claimed\" until manual operator recovery. The diff context does not show a surrounding try/finally that releases the claim on unexpected exceptions, and the state-authority.md doc only documents manual recovery for this scenario.","recommendation":"Wrap the load_job_payload call in a try/except that, on failure, either falls through to the existing mark_cross_run_queue_entry_terminal(failed) path (preserving the pre-fix guarantee that None always terminates the entry) or explicitly releases the queue claim and records a diagnostic failure. Alternatively, confirm the surrounding loop body has a finally block that releases the claim on any exception and cite that structure in the review evidence.","file":"harness/cli.py","line":2548}],"tested":["Requeue precondition blocks when referenced job status != \"queued\" (diff + test_recover_requeue_requires_referenced_job_to_be_queued)","Already-terminal referenced job mirrors succeeded status and is skipped, not failed (diff + test_cross_run_queue_run_once_mirrors_already_terminal_referenced_job)","Atomic entry creation via entry_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=False) replacing check-then-act exists() (diff)","Cleanup-on-failure: except Exception -> shutil.rmtree(entry_dir) re-raises (diff)","Draft202012Validator.check_schema added to static contract schema loop (diff)","Worker-id authorization: unauthorized worker returns None, authorized worker claims (test_worker_id_must_be_authorized_to_claim_queue_entry)","Abandon recovery records audit, sets status \"abandoned\", clears claim_owner, removes claim.lock (test_recover_abandon_records_audit_and_clears_claim)","CLI commands queue-cross-run-job and run-cross-run-queue appear in --help (test_phase9a_cross_run_queue_cli_commands_exist)","evidence.md documents queue files as control/audit artifacts not auto-indexed (diff)","state-authority.md documents queue leases are diagnostic-only, no auto-steal, manual recovery required (diff)"],"not_tested":["Full unittest discover execution (verification summary claims 330 pass, 1 skip — not independently confirmed from diff)","Remote GitHub Actions CI results","Live smoke reproducibility (two owning runs, byte-identical state.json) — claimed in summary but not verifiable from diff","Whether shutil is imported (cleanup-on-failure path uses shutil.rmtree but no test triggers that path)","Full set of values in TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES (not visible in diff; affects terminal mapping accuracy)","mark_cross_run_queue_entry_terminal signature accepts the new terminal_job_status parameter (referenced in new code but definition not in diff)","Whether cross_run_queue_entry_dir is used consistently by all readers/writers replacing the old cross_run_queue_entry_path (structural layout change to entries/<id>/entry.json)","Whether queue iteration handles entries whose directory exists but entry.json is absent after a crash mid-creation","Whether the run-once loop body has a finally/except that releases the queue claim on unexpected exceptions (only partial context visible)","Whether append_cross_run_queue_event is atomic (partial event line risk on crash)"],"residual_risks":["Local filesystem atomicity only: mkdir-based claims and atomic writes are not proof for network shares or cloud queues — explicitly documented as a non-goal in Phase 9A but remains an architectural limitation for any future multi-machine deployment.","Crash between entry_dir.mkdir and write_json_atomic can leave a directory with no entry.json; queue iteration robustness for this state is not verifiable from the diff.","Stuck \"claimed\"/\"running\" queue entries require explicit manual recovery (no auto-steal/reap); operators must run recover_cross_run_queue_entry with confirm=True. This is by design but creates an operational burden if workers crash frequently.","The new load_job_payload calls in run-once and recover paths assume the referenced job.json exists and is well-formed at call time; a narrow TOCTOU window exists between try_claim_job/load and the status read.","If TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES includes non-failure terminal states (skipped/abandoned), the current mapping to \"failed\" produces semantically inaccurate queue audit records.","shutil import for the entry-creation cleanup path is assumed present but not confirmed from the diff; if absent, the except-Exception block would raise NameError instead of cleaning up, though this only triggers on validation/write/event failures which may be rare."]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c6a6ef83-ae1d-42bf-9cbb-17091f6bf443"}
